{"type":"message","id":"76f31371","parentId":"ad438ea6","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:11:49.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying that \"来福来财\" is the main session/agent. So the issue is that the main session (来福来财) is not replying to messages. Let me check the main session status more carefully.\n\nLooking at the session list, the main session was last active \"1m ago\" but the current session (feishu-assistant) is the one responding. Wait - the user is sending messages to the feishu-assistant account, but they expect the \"main\" agent to respond.\n\nActually, looking at the status output again: there are 2 Feishu accounts configured. The `main` account in Feishu config maps to the `main` agent. The `feishu-assistant` account maps to... actually looking at the session list, both accounts seem to route to the main session.\n \nSo the real question is whether \"来福来财\" is its own separate Feishu bot app, or if it's the same as the main session. The user just confirmed it's the main, so I need to check if the main session is actually responding to messages or if there's a routing issue between the Feishu account and the agent.\n\nLooking at the recent activity timestamps, the main session shows \"1h ago\" which seems off. But more importantly, the real problem might be that the main session is stuck in a long-running task and not yielding back to process new messages—I did a sessions_list call earlier that returned 63 active sessions, so there's definitely something happening there.\n\nThe user is saying the main session isn't responding, which could mean it's either blocked waiting for me to finish, or the feishu channel is somehow routing to the wrong agent. Since the current conversation is with feishu-assistant, I should clarify whether messages should be going to main instead, and then dig into what's actually preventing the main session from responding. The user confirmed that \"来福来财就是main\" - so they're pinging the main agent through feishu, but it's not responding. The issue is likely that the main session is either busy running a task (the quant system work) or the feishu routing isn't set up correctly to reach it. I need to check if main is actually running something or if there's a configuration problem preventing it from receiving messages. the main session is processing a task and not yielding. Let me check if there are any running exec processes or if the main session is truly stuck.\n\nActually, looking at the situation more carefully - the feishu-assistant (周到) is responding fine. The user is saying \"来福来财\" (main) is not replying. These are two different agents. The user probably sends messages to both, but only 周到 is replying.\n\nThe issue might be that the main session is blocked/slow, or the main session's feishu channel has some issue.\n\nLet me just check the main session directly to see if it's responsive.\n\nActually, I think the simplest thing to do is: check if the main session is stuck somewhere, and if so, figure out how to unstick it. The user said \"来福来财不回复\" - so I should investigate whether main is blocked on a task or just taking too long to respond.","thinkingSignature":"9166a6d9b4987a7b05efd742994ab151dcd0f5cf44df333981893b7aab35d26c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yskaulkwvu3f_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":5,"messageLimit":2}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80,"output":704,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":35081,"totalTokens":35865,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773922287788}}
