{"type":"message","id":"5ab23e4b","parentId":"6e4ba100","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:12:11.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that the current session IS actually the main session (agent=main, channel=feishu, accountId=feishu-assistant). And it was updated just now (timestamp 1773922287476 = 20:11 today). So the main session IS responding.\n\nBut the user is saying \"来福来财不回复我消息\". This is confusing. Let me think...\n\nWait - maybe the issue is different. Maybe the user is sending messages to the 来福来财 bot (main) but getting no response, while 周到 (feishu-assistant) IS responding. So there are two different bots:\n\n1. 周到 (feishu-assistant) - responding\n\n\n2. 来福来财 (main) - not responding\n\nThe session I'm looking at shows \"abortedLastRun: false\" and it IS receiving messages, so it's not that main isn't running at all. Maybe there's a different 来福来财 instance or the user is confused about which bot they're talking to.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the current conversation IS main (agent=main, session updated just now at 20:11), and I AM responding. So why is the user saying \"来福来财不回复我消息\"?\n\nI'm trying to figure out if maybe the user contacted 来福来财 directly and got no response, but then reached out to 周到 instead, who escalated it to me. Or perhaps there's a separate 来福来财 instance that I'm not seeing in the current session list. The user might be confused about which assistant they're talking to, or the real issue is that the 来福来财 account isn't properly configured to receive DMs from users.\n\nLooking at the session details, I see the message went to feishu-assistant, which suggests there are two separate Feishu bot apps running - 周到 on one app and 来福来财 on another - and the user is saying 来福来财 isn't responding. But when the user sends a message to 来福来财, it's actually coming to me (the main session) since I'm agent=main. So either the user sent to the wrong account, or there's a routing issue where messages to 来福来财 are somehow being handled by the feishu-assistant account instead. The issue is that the user's message came through feishu-assistant (周到), not main (来福来财), which suggests the routing might be configured to route all DMs to feishu-assistant first. But the user is saying main isn't replying at all, so I need to clarify whether main has a separate Feishu bot or if messages should be going through 周到 instead. The user's most recent complaint is clear though—\"来福来财\" isn't responding, so I should focus on addressing that directly rather than trying to understand the routing complexity. The real issue might be that the user is sending messages to a different bot or channel than where I'm actually responding, or there's confusion about which interface they should be using. I should just directly ask them where they're messaging \"来福来财\" to understand the disconnect.","thinkingSignature":"7ed8af739f7e61428bda213d9cf4b1c7f0142a02d849a61f4971d0e79d925ced"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了。你说的\"来福来财\"就是 `agent=main` 这个会话。但从系统来看，当前这条消息就是从 main 过来的——而且 main 现在正在回复你。\n\n那问题可能是：你之前某次发给来福来财，它没回。请问：\n\n**你是从哪里发给来福来财的？**\n- 飞书里的哪个机器人/哪个对话？\n- 还是 OpenClaw 的网页界面？\n\n这样我才能定位是\"发了但没到\"还是\"到了没回\"。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13344,"output":745,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38382,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773922309313}}
