an is to generate a cancellation plan for each stock, show it to the user for approval, then create a new journal entry that sells these holdings at their current prices to bring everything back to cash. I should create a rollback script to apply these corrections at current prices, then show the user the specific execution plan before implementing it. The real issue here is that the halt signal wasn't recognized early enough, so the simulation ended up buying when it shouldn't have—I need to make sure the user understands this timing problem before we proceed with the correction.","thinkingSignature":"3763e82dab1876a0ccdac38632dfa9e1bd8943a4701758425fb11acf8a8e9d41"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了。模拟盘在早盘 09:27 执行了 3 笔买入，但系统在盘中才认识到这是个错误。\n\n当前这三笔持仓（aggressive）的实时价格：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_snvfwn3jw3ar_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, re\nstocks = ['sz002025','sz002151','sz002173']\nfor s in stocks:\n    url = f'http://qt.gtimg.cn/q={s}'\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=8) as resp:\n            text = resp.read().decode('gbk', errors='ignore')\n        m = re.match(r'v_\\w+=\\\"(.*)\\\";', text.strip())\n        if m:\n            f = m.group(1).split('~')\n            print(f'{f[1]}({s}): 现价={f[3]} 涨幅={f[32]}%')\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'{s}: error {e}')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95134,"output":1130,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773929144315}}
