{"type":"message","id":"2ba19705","parentId":"d146a0fa","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:08:03.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Eastmoney API is blocked by proxy. This is the same issue we saw earlier - the network has proxy issues for external connections. \n\nThe user's network seems to have issues connecting to Eastmoney's APIs. Let me try another approach - maybe I can get sector data from a different source, or I can try to use a different API.\n\nActually, let me think about what real-time data sources are available:1. Tencent stock API (we've been using `qt.gtimg.cn` successfully) - for individual stocks2. AkShare - for sector data, but eastmoney connection is blocked\n3. 同花顺 - probably also blocked given network issues\n\nLet me try to get sector data from a different source. Maybe I can try using a different method to get sector data.Actually, let me check what data sources are available. \n\nI could try the ths (同花顺) data provider, but I suspect it might have the same connectivity issues. Given the network constraints, I'm limited in what I can fetch right now - let me see if there's another angle or data source I haven't tried yet.","thinkingSignature":"ae18b86b87d4ca2c84cf3b169a1ffa432c0181a5cf0d6faba9a79d31e133d5b4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kipyu9qc31ub_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis && python3 -c \"\nfrom data_provider.ths_market_bridge import ThsMarketFetcher\nfetcher = ThsMarketFetcher()\n# 试板块数据\nimport asyncio\nasync def test():\n    try:\n        result = await fetcher.get_sector_list()\n        print('sector list result:', str(result)[:300])\n    except Exception as e:\n        print('error:', e)\nasyncio.run(test())\n\" 2>&1 | head -20","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":100005,"output":371,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124669,"cos