{"type":"message","id":"c9f48b79","parentId":"63258ceb","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:28:08.496Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`index_classify` works! But it gives index classification, not sector data. Let me check if there's a way to get sector/industry data from Tushare. Actually, the most reliable way might be to use `ths` market data through the `ths_market_bridge.py` - but that needs `thsdata` module. Let me check if I can install it via pip from a different source.Actually, let me try a different approach. The key issue is that the heatmap needs sector-level data. Instead of relying on a stale CSV, let me:\n\n1. Use Tushare to get all stocks' daily data for today\n2. Use the industry classification from `index_classify` or another source\n\n\n3. Group stocks by industry and calculate sector performance from the individual stock data. Though with nearly 5500 stocks this could be slow, so let me first check if there's a pre-built sector endpoint available - Tushare might offer `pro.fund_sector()` or similar through their pro API.","thinkingSignature":"673af67a512155687d60490aa230e396515ef991f1bd2a2676029694fd68bfd9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hfdiaglutfj7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"TUSHARE_TOKEN='fa7fe5039b58853bd0df3fc31f1770fc4a8cfaa79c6bff0473829bbc' python3 -c \"\nimport tushare as ts\npro = ts.pro_api('fa7fe5039b58853bd0df3fc31f1770fc4a8cfaa79c6bff0473829bbc')\n\n# 试 bak_basic 中有行业字段\ndf = pro.bak_basic(date='20260319', fields='name,industry,close,pct_change')\nprint(df.columns.tolist())\nprint(df[df['industry'].notna()].head(5).to_string())\nprint('有行业字段的:', df[df['industry'].notna()].shape)\n\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":110344,"output":418,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135055,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177