{"type":"message","id":"6f0202f0","parentId":"512d1e08","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:34:03.912Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current structure. The `_prewrite_guard_or_die` function calls the CLI of `prewrite_paper_guard.py` which does the blocking check. The issue is that:\n\n1. `run_prewrite_guard(...)` generates the guard report with `halt_new_buy` info\n2. `_prewrite_guard_or_die(...)` calls the guard script CLI to actually enforce the block\n\nBut the guard script only checks for `halt_new_buy` - it doesn't check for runtime state of the system. The \"深层阻断\" might mean:\n- The guard should check more conditions before allowing account writes\n- Or the guard should be integrated at more points in the execution flow\n\n\n- The core issue is that today the guard failed to prevent the simulated account from executing BUY orders when runtime was halted, which is exactly what \"深层阻断\" (deep blocking) should have prevented.\n\nLooking at how the script gets invoked, I need to trace the execution flow to understand where the blocking logic should actually be enforced rather than just checking runtime state.","thinkingSignature":"9a4926f6da8f3c3b28bb99ac2f493707f55606ec7b21d374c4c5610fb7e37895"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_smn99qyuke4m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def main\\|def run_sim\\|def rebuild\\|prewrite_guard\\|paper_trading_sim\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109970,"output":292,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134555,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773930828728}}
