{"type":"message","id":"69ae2602","parentId":"a373ad93","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:34:37.764Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ckuatzerpi78_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nfor ENV_FILE in \\\n  \"$ROOT/.env.tushare\" \\\n  \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/.env.tushare\"\ndo\n  if [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n    # shellcheck disable=SC1090\n    source \"$ENV_FILE\"\n  fi\ndone\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\n\ncheck_runtime_halt_before_profiles() {\n  local runtime_file=\"${REPORT_DIR}/runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n  if [[ ! -f \"$runtime_file\" ]]; then\n    return 0\n  fi\n  local halt\n  halt=\"$(python3 - \"$runtime_file\" \"$DATE_TAG\" <<'PY2'\nimport json, sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path(sys.argv[1])\ndate_tag=sys.argv[2]\nobj=json.loads(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\nlatest=obj.get('latest_runtime') or {}\nif str(obj.get('date_tag') or '') != str(date_tag):\n    print('0')\nelse:\n    print('1' if latest.get('halt_new_buy') else '0')\nPY2\n)\"\n  if [[ \"$halt\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[BLOCK] runtime halt_new_buy=true; skip paper profile execution before account write\"\n    return 2\n  fi\n  return 0\n}\n\nTICKETS_FILE=\"${2:-}\"\nRETRY_MAX=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_MAX:-2}\"\nRETRY_SLEEP_SEC=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_SLEEP_SEC:-5}\"\nLIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG=\"$ROOT/config/live_scheduler_v1.json\"\nTODAY_TAG=\"$(date +%Y%m%d)\"\nLIVE_SYSTEM_FILE=\"$ROOT/research/reports/live_system_v1_${DATE_TAG}.json\"\n\nread_live_sizing() {\n  python3 - \"$LIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG\" <<'PY'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ncfg_path = Path(sys.argv[1])\npayload = json.loads(cfg_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")) if cfg_path.exists() else {}\nprint(payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000))\nprint(payload.get(\"account_nav\", payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000)))\nPY\n}\n\nensure_same_day_merged_signals() {\n  local sizing available_cash account_nav\n  sizing=\"$(read_live_sizing)\"\n  available_cash=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '1p')\"\n  account_nav=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '2p')\"\n  echo \"[INFO] missing merged_signals, materializing same-day live signal chain date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  python3 scripts/prepare_live_signal_tickets.py \\\n    --date \"$DATE_TAG\" \\\n    --available-cash \"$available_cash\" \\\n    --account-nav \"$account_nav\"\n}\n\nensure_same_day_live_system() {\n  if [[ \"$DATE_TAG\" != \"$TODAY_TAG\" ]]; then\n    return 0\n  fi\n  echo \"[INFO] missing live_system, materializing same-day live system date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  python3 scripts/run_live_system_v1.py\n}\n\nMERGED_FILE=\"$ROOT/signals/merged/merged_signals_${DATE_TAG}.csv\"\ncheck_runtime_halt_before_profiles || exit $?\n\nif [[ \"${FORCE_REFRESH:-0}\" == \"1\" || ! -f \"$LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\" ]]; then\n  ensure_same_day_live_system\nfi\n\nif [[ ! -f \"$LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[ERROR] 缺少当日 live_system: $LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\"\n  exit 2\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"$TICKETS_FILE\" && ! -f \"$MERGED_FILE\" ]]; then\n  ensure_same_day_merged_signals\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"$TICKETS_FILE\" && ! -f \"$MERGED_FILE\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[ERROR] 缺少当日 merged_signals: $MERGED_FILE\"\n  exit 2\nfi\n\nrun_once() {\n  if [[ -n \"$TICKETS_FILE\" ]]; then\n    bash scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh \"$DATE_TAG\" \"$TICKETS_FILE\"\n  else\n    bash scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh \"$DATE_TAG\"\n  fi\n}\n\nattempt=1\nwhile (( attempt <= RETRY_MAX )); do\n  echo \"[RUN] paper_profiles attempt ${attempt}/${RETRY_MAX} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  run_once\n  code=$?\n  if (( code == 0 )); then\n    echo \"[OK] paper_profiles updated date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    echo \"- defensive: research/reports/paper_defensive_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- balanced: research/reports/paper_balanced_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- aggressive: research/reports/paper_aggressive_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- comparison: research/reports/paper_profiles_comparison_latest.html\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  if (( attempt >= RETRY_MAX )); then\n    echo \"[FAIL] paper_profiles exit=${code} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    exit \"$code\"\n  fi\n  echo \"[RETRY] paper_profiles exit=${code}; sleep ${RETRY_SLEEP_SEC}s\"\n  sleep \"$RETRY_SLEEP_SEC\"\n  attempt=$((attempt + 1))\ndone\none\natest.html\"\n    echo \"- comparison: research/reports/paper_profiles_comparison_latest.html\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  if (( attempt >= RETRY_MAX )); then\n    echo \"[FAIL] paper_profiles exit=${code} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    exit \"$code\"\n  fi\n  echo \"[RETRY] paper_profiles exit=${code}; sleep ${RETRY_SLEEP_SEC}s\"\n  sleep \"$RETRY_SLEEP_SEC\"\n  attempt=$((attempt + 1))\ndone\n\n\n# PREWRITE_GUARD_CHECK\nfor guard_profile in defensive balanced aggressive; do\n  account_json=\"${REPORT_DIR}/paper_${guard_profile}_account_v1_${DATE_TAG}.json\"\n  if [[ -f \"$account_json\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[INFO] validating account guard for ${guard_profile}: $account_json\"\n    python3 scripts/prewrite_paper_guard.py --date \"$DATE_TAG\" --profile \"$guard_profile\" --account-json \"$account_json\"\n  fi\ndone"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nfor ENV_FILE in \\\n  \"$ROOT/.env.tushare\" \\\n  \"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/.env.tushare\"\ndo\n  if [[ -f \"$ENV_FILE\" ]]; then\n    # shellcheck disable=SC1090\n    source \"$ENV_FILE\"\n  fi\ndone\n\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\n\ncheck_runtime_halt_before_profiles() {\n  local runtime_file=\"${REPORT_DIR}/runtime_risk_state_latest.json\"\n  if [[ ! -f \"$runtime_file\" ]]; then\n    return 0\n  fi\n  local halt\n  halt=\"$(python3 - \"$runtime_file\" \"$DATE_TAG\" <<'PY2'\nimport json, sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path(sys.argv[1])\ndate_tag=sys.argv[2]\nobj=json.loads(p.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\nlatest=obj.get('latest_runtime') or {}\nif str(obj.get('date_tag') or '') != str(date_tag):\n    print('0')\nelse:\n    print('1' if latest.get('halt_new_buy') else '0')\nPY2\n)\"\n  if [[ \"$halt\" == \"1\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[BLOCK] runtime halt_new_buy=true; skip paper profile execution before account write\"\n    return 2\n  fi\n  return 0\n}\n\nTICKETS_FILE=\"${2:-}\"\nRETRY_MAX=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_MAX:-2}\"\nRETRY_SLEEP_SEC=\"${PAPER_PROFILES_RETRY_SLEEP_SEC:-5}\"\nLIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG=\"$ROOT/config/live_scheduler_v1.json\"\nTODAY_TAG=\"$(date +%Y%m%d)\"\nLIVE_SYSTEM_FILE=\"$ROOT/research/reports/live_system_v1_${DATE_TAG}.json\"\n\nread_live_sizing() {\n  python3 - \"$LIVE_SCHEDULER_CFG\" <<'PY'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\ncfg_path = Path(sys.argv[1])\npayload = json.loads(cfg_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")) if cfg_path.exists() else {}\nprint(payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000))\nprint(payload.get(\"account_nav\", payload.get(\"available_cash\", 1000000)))\nPY\n}\n\nensure_same_day_merged_signals() {\n  local sizing available_cash account_nav\n  sizing=\"$(read_live_sizing)\"\n  available_cash=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '1p')\"\n  account_nav=\"$(printf '%s\\n' \"$sizing\" | sed -n '2p')\"\n  echo \"[INFO] missing merged_signals, materializing same-day live signal chain date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  python3 scripts/prepare_live_signal_tickets.py \\\n    --date \"$DATE_TAG\" \\\n    --available-cash \"$available_cash\" \\\n    --account-nav \"$account_nav\"\n}\n\nensure_same_day_live_system() {\n  if [[ \"$DATE_TAG\" != \"$TODAY_TAG\" ]]; then\n    return 0\n  fi\n  echo \"[INFO] missing live_system, materializing same-day live system date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  python3 scripts/run_live_system_v1.py\n}\n\nMERGED_FILE=\"$ROOT/signals/merged/merged_signals_${DATE_TAG}.csv\"\ncheck_runtime_halt_before_profiles || exit $?\n\nif [[ \"${FORCE_REFRESH:-0}\" == \"1\" || ! -f \"$LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\" ]]; then\n  ensure_same_day_live_system\nfi\n\nif [[ ! -f \"$LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[ERROR] 缺少当日 live_system: $LIVE_SYSTEM_FILE\"\n  exit 2\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"$TICKETS_FILE\" && ! -f \"$MERGED_FILE\" ]]; then\n  ensure_same_day_merged_signals\nfi\n\nif [[ -z \"$TICKETS_FILE\" && ! -f \"$MERGED_FILE\" ]]; then\n  echo \"[ERROR] 缺少当日 merged_signals: $MERGED_FILE\"\n  exit 2\nfi\n\nrun_once() {\n  if [[ -n \"$TICKETS_FILE\" ]]; then\n    bash scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh \"$DATE_TAG\" \"$TICKETS_FILE\"\n  else\n    bash scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh \"$DATE_TAG\"\n  fi\n}\n\nattempt=1\nwhile (( attempt <= RETRY_MAX )); do\n  echo \"[RUN] paper_profiles attempt ${attempt}/${RETRY_MAX} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n  run_once\n  code=$?\n  if (( code == 0 )); then\n    echo \"[OK] paper_profiles updated date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    echo \"- defensive: research/reports/paper_defensive_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- balanced: research/reports/paper_balanced_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- aggressive: research/reports/paper_aggressive_trading_dashboard_latest.html\"\n    echo \"- comparison: research/reports/paper_profiles_comparison_latest.html\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  if (( attempt >= RETRY_MAX )); then\n    echo \"[FAIL] paper_profiles exit=${code} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    exit \"$code\"\n  fi\n  echo \"[RETRY] paper_profiles exit=${code}; sleep ${RETRY_SLEEP_SEC}s\"\n  sleep \"$RETRY_SLEEP_SEC\"\n  attempt=$((attempt + 1))\ndone\none\natest.html\"\n    echo \"- comparison: research/reports/paper_profiles_comparison_latest.html\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  if (( attempt >= RETRY_MAX )); then\n    echo \"[FAIL] paper_profiles exit=${code} date=${DATE_TAG}\"\n    exit \"$code\"\n  fi\n  echo \"[RETRY] paper_profiles exit=${code}; sleep ${RETRY_SLEEP_SEC}s\"\n  sleep \"$RETRY_SLEEP_SEC\"\n  attempt=$((attempt + 1))\ndone\n\n\n# PREWRITE_GUARD_CHECK\nfor guard_profile in defensive balanced aggressive; do\n  account_json=\"${REPORT_DIR}/paper_${guard_profile}_account_v1_${DATE_TAG}.json\"\n  if [[ -f \"$account_json\" ]]; then\n    echo \"[INFO] validating account guard for ${guard_profile}: $account_json\"\n    python3 scripts/prewrite_paper_guard.py --date \"$DATE_TAG\" --profile \"$guard_profile\" --account-json \"$account_json\"\n  fi\ndone","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773930877750}}
{"type":"message","id":"59067c81","parentId":"69ae2602","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:01.300Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue! There are TWO levels of guard:1. Shell-level `check_runtime_halt_before_profiles()` - checks `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` for `halt_new_buy` before running profiles2. Python-level `_prewrite_guard_or_die()` - called inside `rebuild_account()` which is inside `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh`\n\nBut looking at the end of the script, there's also a `PREWRITE_GUARD_CHECK` that validates account files AFTER they're generated. This is a post-write check, not a pre-write block.\n\nThe key issue is: what happened this morning that allowed the BUY orders to be written despite `halt_new_buy=true`?\n \nSo the shell guard runs before any profiles are executed, but if `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` doesn't exist or has stale data, it passes through anyway. Then the Python guard in `_prewrite_guard_or_die()` checks whether `halt_new_buy=true` for today's date before allowing the account to be written, but by that point it's already too late—the guard only raises an error, it doesn't actually prevent the write from happening.\n\nLooking at the actual code flow, the guard function gets called but its return value isn't being checked, so even if it detected a halt condition and returned a non-zero code, the script would continue executing and write the account file anyway. The positions get written first, then the account payload is constructed, and then the guard runs—but there's no conditional logic stopping the write if the guard fails.\n\nFor true deep blocking at the account write level, I need to add an explicit check that raises an exception if the halt flag is active. The existing guard checks a hardcoded halt condition, but it should be reading the current runtime state dynamically instead of relying on pre-computed data.\n\nThe deeper issue is that the positions CSV and account JSON are being persisted to disk even when they contain today's BUY trades under halt conditions—that's the violation that needs to be prevented at the source, not just validated afterward. 实际上看，`rebuild_account()`调用`run_prewrite_guard()`，它检查的是**今天的 journal 记录**中是否有 BUY（halt时应该没有）。但 journal 本身是由之前生成的——所以如果 journal 是在 halt 之前生成的，guard 就不会阻止它。问题可能更深层：我需要查看 guard 具体在检查什么。","thinkingSignature":"975d036b255fa3890e8b5adb1e0e9a95cf0b42eace45e479ca9c7bf89b86928b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9z0cfitkztp8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prewrite_paper_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":107579,"output":539,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773930877770}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf7a0358","parentId":"59067c81","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:01.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9z0cfitkztp8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = ROOT / 'research' / 'reports'\nRUNTIME_STATE = REPORT_DIR / 'runtime_risk_state_latest.json'\n\n\ndef load_json(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return {}\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\n\ndef evaluate_guard(\n    *,\n    date_tag: str,\n    profile: str,\n    account: dict[str, Any],\n    account_json: str,\n    runtime_obj: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    runtime_payload = runtime_obj or load_json(RUNTIME_STATE)\n    latest_runtime = runtime_payload.get('latest_runtime') or {}\n    runtime_date = str(runtime_payload.get('date_tag') or '')\n    halt_new_buy = bool(latest_runtime.get('halt_new_buy')) if runtime_date == date_tag else False\n\n    issues: list[str] = []\n    if halt_new_buy:\n        today_buy_count = int(account.get('today_buy_count') or 0)\n        if today_buy_count > 0:\n            issues.append(f'today_buy_count={today_buy_count} under halt')\n\n    return {\n        'generated_at': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'),\n        'date_tag': date_tag,\n        'profile': profile,\n        'account_json': str(account_json),\n        'runtime_state': str(RUNTIME_STATE),\n        'halt_new_buy': halt_new_buy,\n        'issues': issues,\n        'status': 'PASS' if not issues else 'BLOCK',\n    }\n\n\ndef write_guard_report(report_dir: Path, profile: str, date_tag: str, payload: dict[str, Any]) -> Path:\n    safe_profile = str(profile or 'default').strip() or 'default'\n    out = report_dir / f'prewrite_paper_guard_{safe_profile}_{date_tag}.json'\n    out.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding='utf-8')\n    return out\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='写账户前二次校验：halt 状态下禁止保留新增买入')\n    ap.add_argument('--date', default=datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d'))\n    ap.add_argument('--profile', required=True, choices=['defensive','balanced','aggressive'])\n    ap.add_argument('--account-json', required=True)\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    account_path = Path(args.account_json)\n    account = load_json(account_path)\n    payload = evaluate_guard(\n        date_tag=args.date,\n        profile=args.profile,\n        account=account,\n        account_json=str(account_path),\n    )\n    write_guard_report(REPORT_DIR, args.profile, args.date, payload)\n    print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n    if payload.get('issues'):\n        raise SystemExit(2)\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nREPORT_DIR = ROOT / 'research' / 'reports'\nRUNTIME_STATE = REPORT_DIR / 'runtime_risk_state_latest.json'\n\n\ndef load_json(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return {}\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n\n\ndef evaluate_guard(\n    *,\n    date_tag: str,\n    profile: str,\n    account: dict[str, Any],\n    account_json: str,\n    runtime_obj: dict[str, Any] | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    runtime_payload = runtime_obj or load_json(RUNTIME_STATE)\n    latest_runtime = runtime_payload.get('latest_runtime') or {}\n    runtime_date = str(runtime_payload.get('date_tag') or '')\n    halt_new_buy = bool(latest_runtime.get('halt_new_buy')) if runtime_date == date_tag else False\n\n    issues: list[str] = []\n    if halt_new_buy:\n        today_buy_count = int(account.get('today_buy_count') or 0)\n        if today_buy_count > 0:\n            issues.append(f'today_buy_count={today_buy_count} under halt')\n\n    return {\n        'generated_at': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'),\n        'date_tag': date_tag,\n        'profile': profile,\n        'account_json': str(account_json),\n        'runtime_state': str(RUNTIME_STATE),\n        'halt_new_buy': halt_new_buy,\n        'issues': issues,\n        'status': 'PASS' if not issues else 'BLOCK',\n    }\n\n\ndef write_guard_report(report_dir: Path, profile: str, date_tag: str, payload: dict[str, Any]) -> Path:\n    safe_profile = str(profile or 'default').strip() or 'default'\n    out = report_dir / f'prewrite_paper_guard_{safe_profile}_{date_tag}.json'\n    out.write_text(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding='utf-8')\n    return out\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='写账户前二次校验：halt 状态下禁止保留新增买入')\n    ap.add_argument('--date', default=datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d'))\n    ap.add_argument('--profile', required=True, choices=['defensive','balanced','aggressive'])\n    ap.add_argument('--account-json', required=True)\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    account_path = Path(args.account_json)\n    account = load_json(account_path)\n    payload = evaluate_guard(\n        date_tag=args.date,\n        profile=args.profile,\n        account=account,\n        account_json=str(account_path),\n    )\n    write_guard_report(REPORT_DIR, args.profile, args.date, payload)\n    print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n    if payload.get('issues'):\n        raise SystemExit(2)\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773930901355}}
{"type":"message","id":"9942ab11","parentId":"bf7a0358","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:20.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The `evaluate_guard` function:1. Checks `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` for `halt_new_buy` for the given date\n2. If `halt_new_buy=True` and `today_buy_count > 0`, adds an issue\n\nThe guard is called in TWO places:1. Inside `rebuild_account()` in `run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py` - via `_prewrite_guard_or_die()`\n2. In the shell script's `PREWRITE_GUARD_CHECK` - post-write validation\n\nThe problem is: the guard only raises `SystemExit(2)` in `main()`, but when called via `_prewrite_guard_or_die()`, the function `evaluate_guard()` is called without checking its result! The guard subprocess just raises if `payload.get('issues')` is non-empty. BUT - there's a critical issue: the guard evaluates `halt_new_buy` from `runtime_risk_state_latest.json`, but if that file was written BEFORE the halt was triggered (i.e., the runtime state was computed earlier in the morning before the halt was set), then the guard would not detect the halt.\n \nSo the timing issue is that `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` might contain stale data—it could have been written before the halt was triggered, meaning the guard wouldn't catch the violation. But looking at today's account, `today_buy_count` is 3, so if the guard had properly detected `halt_new_buy=True`, it should have flagged the issue and raised an error, yet it didn't.\n\nThe root cause seems to be that `rebuild_account()` is being called to rebuild today's account from the journal, which already contains 3 BUY records from this morning's paper trading. When the guard evaluates the halt condition and sees these 3 buys, it should fail. I need to trace where `run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh` actually invokes `run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py` to understand why the guard didn't catch this.","thinkingSignature":"532515719c4b469427307f4f7d124bf2d788eed928ab5ab5a1ab9284b18e1d23"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v91fny80eb11_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":106684,"output":481,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131458,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773930901369}}
{"type":"message","id":"622a0596","parentId":"9942ab11","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:20.881Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v91fny80eb11_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nTICKETS_FILE=\"${2:-}\"\n\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nrun_profile() {\n  local config_file=\"$1\"\n  local orders_file\n  local prep_cmd=(python3 scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py --config \"$config_file\" --date \"$DATE_TAG\")\n  if [[ -n \"$TICKETS_FILE\" ]]; then\n    prep_cmd+=(--tickets \"$TICKETS_FILE\")\n  fi\n\n  \"${prep_cmd[@]}\"\n\n  orders_file=\"$(python3 - \"$config_file\" \"$DATE_TAG\" <<'PY'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nproject_root = Path.cwd()\nsys.path.insert(0, str(project_root / \"scripts\"))\nfrom paper_profile_utils import profile_slug_from_config, report_path\n\ncfg = json.loads(Path(sys.argv[1]).read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\ndate_tag = sys.argv[2]\nslug = profile_slug_from_config(cfg)\nprint(report_path(project_root / \"research\" / \"reports\", \"orders\", profile_slug=slug, date_tag=date_tag))\nPY\n)\"\n\n  python3 scripts/run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py --config \"$config_file\" --date \"$DATE_TAG\" --orders \"$orders_file\"\n  python3 scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py --config \"$config_file\"\n}\n\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_defensive_v1.json\"\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_balanced_v1.json\"\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json\"\n\npython3 scripts/generate_paper_trading_comparison_dashboard.py \\\n  --configs \\\n    config/paper_trading_defensive_v1.json \\\n    config/paper_trading_balanced_v1.json \\\n    config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json\n\npython3 scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py --date \"$DATE_TAG\"\npython3 scripts/generate_dashboard_portal.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\nROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nDATE_TAG=\"${1:-$(date +%Y%m%d)}\"\nTICKETS_FILE=\"${2:-}\"\n\ncd \"$ROOT\"\n\nrun_profile() {\n  local config_file=\"$1\"\n  local orders_file\n  local prep_cmd=(python3 scripts/prepare_paper_orders_v1.py --config \"$config_file\" --date \"$DATE_TAG\")\n  if [[ -n \"$TICKETS_FILE\" ]]; then\n    prep_cmd+=(--tickets \"$TICKETS_FILE\")\n  fi\n\n  \"${prep_cmd[@]}\"\n\n  orders_file=\"$(python3 - \"$config_file\" \"$DATE_TAG\" <<'PY'\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nproject_root = Path.cwd()\nsys.path.insert(0, str(project_root / \"scripts\"))\nfrom paper_profile_utils import profile_slug_from_config, report_path\n\ncfg = json.loads(Path(sys.argv[1]).read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\ndate_tag = sys.argv[2]\nslug = profile_slug_from_config(cfg)\nprint(report_path(project_root / \"research\" / \"reports\", \"orders\", profile_slug=slug, date_tag=date_tag))\nPY\n)\"\n\n  python3 scripts/run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py --config \"$config_file\" --date \"$DATE_TAG\" --orders \"$orders_file\"\n  python3 scripts/generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py --config \"$config_file\"\n}\n\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_defensive_v1.json\"\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_balanced_v1.json\"\nrun_profile \"config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json\"\n\npython3 scripts/generate_paper_trading_comparison_dashboard.py \\\n  --configs \\\n    config/paper_trading_defensive_v1.json \\\n    config/paper_trading_balanced_v1.json \\\n    config/paper_trading_aggressive_v1.json\n\npython3 scripts/generate_today_stock_strategy_report.py --date \"$DATE_TAG\"\npython3 scripts/generate_dashboard_portal.py","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773930920867}}
{"type":"message","id":"368fa3ec","parentId":"622a0596","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:37.272Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full chain:\n\n1. `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh` calls:\n   - `prepare_paper_orders_v1.py` - prepares orders\n   - `run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py` - rebuilds account (this is where the guard is called via `_prewrite_guard_or_die`)\n   - `generate_paper_trading_dashboard.py`\n   \n2. The `run_paper_trading_profiles_auto_v1.sh` calls:\n   - First calls `check_runtime_halt_before_profiles()` (shell-level)\n   - Then calls `run_paper_trading_profiles_v1.sh`\n   - Then at the end, calls `prewrite_paper_guard.py` for validation\n\nThe real problem is that the Python guard subprocess in `run_paper_trading_sim_v1.py` would only raise an error if `halt_new_buy` is True AND `today_buy_count > 0` in the account, but today's halt was set AFTER the morning execution happened, so the runtime state never caught the violation.\n\nThe solution is to add a deeper pre-write check that compares the account's BUY count against the current runtime state right before actually writing the account file. I need to enhance the guard to pull fresh runtime state data instead of relying on potentially stale snapshots.\n\nWriting the enhanced guard implementation...","thinkingSignature":"277daa255947514c317dd0c5d0131ac651f6f28a699a6d244d444c6d19c85c63"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full picture. The current guard checks the `runtime_risk_state_latest.json` which may have been written before halt was triggered. The deep blocking needs to:\n\n1. Check runtime state at the **actual write moment** (not stale file)\n2. Block if `halt_new_buy=True` and account has BUY count > 0\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jogoym4lz97a_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/prewrite_paper_guard.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-message