{"type":"message","id":"bb9f2e06","parentId":"868b2517","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:40:14.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the problem:\n\nDefault priority: `tencent,akshare_sina,efinance,akshare_em`\n\nTHS and Pytdx are NOT in the default. They need to be explicitly configured in `realtime_source_priority`.\n\nBut more importantly, the entry point scripts (`intraday_market_gate.py`, `intraday_market_breadth.py`, `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py`) are NOT even using `DataFetcherManager`. They're calling their own specific fetchers directly.\n\nSo the fixes needed are:\n\n1. **Update `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py`**: Replace `urllib.request` to Tencent with `DataFetcherManager.get_realtime_quote()` and configure `realtime_source_priority` to put THS/TDX first\n\n\n2. **Update `intraday_market_gate.py`**: Same approach - replace the direct Tencent call with `DataFetcherManager`\n3. **Update `intraday_market_breadth.py`**: This is more complex since it needs breadth data (up count vs down count), which requires fetching all stocks - I need to understand how `get_realtime_breadth` works in the DataFetcherManager","thinkingSignature":"3e8d72d0551f28fe0e20c156af2dfb3ffb7e3921565d9bd7a2405136b4296fe0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_as4uarjmerpi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def get_realtime_breadth\\|def market_breadth\\|def breadth\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/data_provider/base.py 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":110508,"output":320,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773931206610}}
