{"type":"message","id":"6a534df5","parentId":"17257626","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:40:26.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `get_realtime_breadth` method in `DataFetcherManager`. So `intraday_market_breadth.py` will need to keep using its own approach for breadth data (which requires fetching all stocks).\n\nBut for `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py` and `intraday_market_gate.py`, we can switch them to use `DataFetcherManager`.\n\nThe key fix for the user's concern is:\n\n1. For `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py` (and v1): Replace `fetch_quote()` with `DataFetcherManager.get_realtime_quote()` \n\n\n2. Configure `realtime_source_priority` to include THS and Pytdx as higher priority\n\nI should create a plan and show it to the user rather than just implementing changes - the issue is that the unified fetcher was built into `daily_stock_analysis` but the main chain scripts aren't actually using it yet. The most impactful fix would be to switch `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py` to use `DataFetcherManager` and raise the priority of THS/TDX sources.\n\nModifying the entry point script to leverage the unified fetcher instead of hardcoding specific sources like Tencent.","thinkingSignature":"9fe4de493f8e45c68395e18c130fa4ee5f766dc212b0dd4cf0f18d21a3c5e451"},{"type":"text","text":"情况核实完毕，现状确认：\n\n**`DataFetcherManager` 里有 THS/TDX，但主链入口没在用它。**\n\n| 脚本 | 当前数据源 | 统一路由？ |\n|---|---|---|\n| `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py` | `urllib.request` 直连腾讯 | ❌ 未用 |\n| `intraday_market_gate.py` | `urllib.request` 直连腾讯 | ❌ 未用 |\n| `intraday_market_breadth.py` | AkShare + eFinance | ❌ 未用 |\n\n默认优先级是 `tencent,akshare_sina,efinance,akshare_em`，THS/TDX 不在列表里。\n\n我来把 `stock_level_realtime_gate_v2.py` 改成用 `DataFetcherManager`，并把 THS/TDX 配进优先级：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6om0i9n9y73d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"thsdata\\|ThsMarket\\|import\\|ths\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/dat