{"type":"message","id":"4824561c","parentId":"9ddfe961","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:40:38.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `ThsMarketFetcher` requires either:\n1. A running THS terminal application (Windows COM)\n2. The `thsdata/thsdk` Python package (not installed)\n3. The current interpreter with `thsdata/thsdk`\n\nSince `thsdata` is not installed and we don't have a Windows environment, the THS fetcher won't work directly. Let me check what Pytdx requires.\n\nActually, the issue is that `thsdata` package doesn't exist on PyPI. And Pytdx was failing with connection errors earlier.\n\nLet me think about what the user really needs. The user said the THS/TDX has been \"接进统一数据源优先级路由层\" - meaning the code is there, but the actual network connectivity is another matter.\n\n\nSo Pytdx is blocked at the network level with connection refused errors, and THS requires either a Windows-only terminal or the unavailable `thsdata` package. The real bottleneck is that neither of these data sources can actually connect right now.\n\nThe immediate priorities are updating the entry point scripts to use the unified `DataFetcherManager` and ensuring the configuration properly reflects THS/TDX as higher priority options. Even if these sources are temporarily unreachable, making the code structural changes now means the system will automatically leverage them once connectivity is restored.","thinkingSignature":"a827cb0e3ceb0a7f03c5bc16aeb3db41cf2ce65197e30a61f46fa5ded8c62d29"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ljpdddchcn9g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"thsdata\\|THS_SDK\\|ths_terminal\\|ths_exe\\|sdk_path\\|terminal\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/daily_stock_analysis/data_provider/ths_market_fetcher.py 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111453,"output":346,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136092,"cost":{"in