{"type":"message","id":"e9799919","parentId":"d49f49c5","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:49:01.899Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The Tushare fallback worked! \n- AkShare failed (proxy)\n- eFinance failed (proxy)\n- Tushare succeeded: 472 up, 4499 down, 4990 total, up_ratio=0.0946\n\nThis means only 9.5% of stocks were up today - a very bad market day. This matches the sector heatmap we saw (9 up, 101 down sectors).\n\nNow let me commit this and also update the `intraday_market_breadth.py` script to include this Tushare fallback. The script is now working as a 3-source fallback.\n\n\nI'm realizing the Tushare approach actually handles both today's breadth and historical data fine, so I could consolidate the logic to always use Tushare as the primary source since it's proven reliable, with AkShare and eFinance as secondary fallbacks. But the core fix is solid - the 3-source fallback is working correctly.","thinkingSignature":"374b9d9cca60ae825098f4260b34c38dbd7e9067fd1b5b85e8553f562fed6969"},{"type":"text","text":"三源兜底验证成功：\n\n- AkShare：代理阻塞 ❌\n- eFinance：失败 ❌  \n- **Tushare：成功** ✅ — 472上涨 / 4499下跌 / 4990总计，`up_ratio=9.5%`\n\n完全符合今天大盘实际情况。commit：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i63qbysroa39_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && git add quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/scripts/intraday_market_breadth.py && git commit -m \"feat: intraday_market_breadth add Tushare as 3rd fallback source\n\nThree-source fallback: AkShare → eFinance → Tushare\n- AkShare/eFinance blocked by proxy → Tushare fallback triggered successfully\n- Tushare result: 472 up / 4499 down / 4990 total (up_ratio=9.5%)\n- Matches today's market reality (9 sectors up, 101 sectors down)\n- Tushare daily API used as last resort when real-time sources fail\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":115305,"output":430,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheW