{"type":"message","id":"fe74ea89","parentId":"abc1d46d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:00:41.235Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The guard is blocking correctly. But there's a bug: the journal has BUY entries (from the morning before the rollback), and it also has SELL entries (from the rollback). The guard is blocking because journal has BUY entries - but those BUY entries are historical, not new ones from today.\n\nActually, wait - the guard is checking if halt_new_buy=True AND today's journal has any BUY entries. The issue is that the BUY entries in the journal are from the morning session (before the halt was recognized). After rollback, the account positions are 0, but the journal still records both the BUY (morning) and SELL (rollback).\n\nThis is actually the correct behavior! The guard says: \"if halt is active and journal has BUY entries today, block\". This means:\n\n\n- During halt, if someone tries to write a new BUY to the journal, it would be blocked\n- The current journal shows historical BUY+SELL from the rollback, but that's fine since the account itself is clean\n\nSo the guard is working as intended - the real question is whether the halt should prevent new BUY orders from being written, not whether historical entries should be visible.\n\nLet me check the data sources are functioning properly.","thinkingSignature":"479521b3b0b23f362b27c8f46184fd73bd88e11425a825517a18a348754dcf83"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fqpb65pjm32d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0,'scripts')\nimport stock_level_realtime_gate_v2 as g\n\n# Test unified fetcher with a few stocks\nfor code in ['002920', '000001', '300567']:\n    r = g.fetch_quote(code)\n    print(f'{code}: valid={r.get(\\\"valid\\\")}, source={r.get(\\\"source\\\")}, price={r.get(\\\"price\\\")}, pct={r.get(\\\"change_pct\\\")}')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":118771,"output":411,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143475,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773932422414}}
