{"type":"message","id":"e68d8af9","parentId":"32d173e4","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:10:56.796Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the cron jobs. There's a \"23点记忆夜跑\" that runs at 23:00 and reads the day's logs. But that's for memory/learning, not for continuing active tasks.\n\nThe key insight is that there's no automatic \"continue active task\" cron job. The system relies on:\n1. User messages to continue a task\n2. Scheduled cron jobs that do their own things\n3. The ACTIVE_TASK.md as a recovery rail when the session restarts\n\nThe issue the user is describing: after completing one step, the assistant stops and doesn't continue to the next. The ACTIVE_TASK.md mechanism only works when:\n- A new user message comes in\n- The session restarts and reads the ACTIVE_TASK.md\n\n\n- The cron job triggers and loads the ACTIVE_TASK.md to resume\n\nI see there are two task runners - a main session at 23:00 and a Codex at 23:00 - both reading from the same memory checklist. The problem is that neither is designed to automatically resume an interrupted active task chain.\n\nThe ACTIVE_TASK.md only works as a recovery mechanism when there's a session restart, but there's no scheduled trigger that automatically picks up where the current task left off. I need to either modify the 23:00 memory runner to check for active tasks and continue them, add a dedicated cron job that monitors the ACTIVE_TASK.md file, or find another way to ensure tasks resume without waiting for user input.","thinkingSignature":"a13b510f4fa1c94c9c812d4824328dd54dc43ce78c4082d29da79c72514c2d0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_od05gy9kzi0n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/heartbeat-self-improvement.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":118982,"output":348,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143623,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933040574}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1f4fe3a","parentId":"e68d8af9","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:10:56.849Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_od05gy9kzi0n_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Checklist: Heartbeat Self-Improvement\n\n## Command\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/auto_promote_learnings.py --apply --threshold 2\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/auto_extract_skill_drafts.py --threshold 2\n```\n\n## Output\n- `memory/self_improvement_daily_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `memory/self_improvement_autopromote_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `memory/self_improvement_skill_drafts_YYYYMMDD.md`\n\n## Rules\n- [ ] 汇总 `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` / `ERRORS.md` / `FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n- [ ] 统计高优先级待处理项、状态分布、area 分布\n- [ ] 对 `Recurrence-Count >= 2` 的 learning 自动提升到 `AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / SOUL.md`\n- [ ] 对 `Recurrence-Count >= 2` 的 learning 生成 skill 草稿到 `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n- [ ] **只生成草稿，不自动安装**到 `~/.openclaw/skills/`\n- [ ] 无论有无提升项，都主动发飞书 DM 汇报摘要与三个输出文件路径\n- [ ] 若无提升项，明确写“今日无自动提升项”\n- [ ] 若无技能草稿，明确写“今日无技能草稿生成”\n- [ ] 若发生自动提升，汇报被提升条目、目标文件路径、写入是否成功"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"# Checklist: Heartbeat Self-Improvement\n\n## Command\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/generate_daily_report.py\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/auto_promote_learnings.py --apply --threshold 2\npython3 skills/self-improving-agent/scripts/auto_extract_skill_drafts.py --threshold 2\n```\n\n## Output\n- `memory/self_improvement_daily_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `memory/self_improvement_autopromote_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `memory/self_improvement_skill_drafts_YYYYMMDD.md`\n\n## Rules\n- [ ] 汇总 `.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` / `ERRORS.md` / `FEATURE_REQUESTS.md`\n- [ ] 统计高优先级待处理项、状态分布、area 分布\n- [ ] 对 `Recurrence-Count >= 2` 的 learning 自动提升到 `AGENTS.md / TOOLS.md / SOUL.md`\n- [ ] 对 `Recurrence-Count >= 2` 的 learning 生成 skill 草稿到 `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n- [ ] **只生成草稿，不自动安装**到 `~/.openclaw/skills/`\n- [ ] 无论有无提升项，都主动发飞书 DM 汇报摘要与三个输出文件路径\n- [ ] 若无提升项，明确写“今日无自动提升项”\n- [ ] 若无技能草稿，明确写“今日无技能草稿生成”\n- [ ] 若发生自动提升，汇报被提升条目、目标文件路径、写入是否成功","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773933056833}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbcd4697","parentId":"a1f4fe3a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:11:13.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. There's a heartbeat for self-improvement, but not for continuing active tasks.\n\nThe fundamental issue is: the ACTIVE_TASK.md mechanism requires either:\n1. A user message to trigger continuation\n2. A session restart to recover from the file\n\nThere's no automatic trigger that says \"I'm done with step X, now start step Y\".\n\nThe solution would be to create a heartbeat that periodically checks if there's an active task with a \"Next\" item and continues it. But this is complex because heartbeats run in isolated sessions that don't have the conversation context.\n\nHowever, looking at the rules in AGENTS.md more carefully:\n\n> If `scripts/active_task_cli.py` exists, you must use `python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py show --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md` for verification and `python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py advance --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md ...` for atomic state transitions\n\n\nSo the mechanism relies on the assistant using the CLI to update the ACTIVE_TASK.md after each step. But the problem is that after completing a step, the session ends and there's no automatic trigger to pick up the next one. The session itself is the implicit continuation trigger, so without an external trigger mechanism, the task chain just stops.\n\nThe ACTIVE_TASK.md file serves as a recovery checkpoint—if the session restarts, it can pick up where it left off. But in a single continuous session, there's no built-in way to automatically proceed from one step to the next unless I explicitly build that automation. The user is right that the system stops after completing one step, and I need to figure out how to ensure it actually continues through the entire chain.\n\nI think the issue is that my response is ending the conversation when it shouldn't. I should be using `sessions_yield` to hand control back to the orchestrator so it can continue to the next step, rather than sending a final reply that closes out the turn. The agent can't loop on its own after responding, so the orchestrator needs to handle the continuation.","thinkingSignature":"f2a329dbb70ac5a0e088b34c112a33a6c8a74333f6e9ce8d1e7e4b8c22308588"},{"type":"text","text":"问题分析清楚了。\n\n**根本原因**：每步完成后我在回复里直接结束 turn（发消息），没有把控制权交还给调度层，系统在等待下一条用户消息才能继续。\n\n**当前的恢复铁轨**（ACTIVE_TASK.md）只在两种情况下触发：\n1. 用户发新消息\n2. Session 重启后读取\n\n没有自动触发器在步骤之间继续执行。\n\n我来在 heartbeat 里加一个连续任务恢复检查，同时建议一个专门的定时任务：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xyhy5pm0yane_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/heartbeat-quant-ops.md 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119693,"output":557,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":144543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933056854}}
{"type":"message","id":"666dd95d","parentId":"cbcd4697","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:11:13.489Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xyhy5pm0yane_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Checklist: Heartbeat Quant Ops\n\n## 08:50 Morning News Push Check\n\n### State File\n```bash\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/global_market_morning_0850_state.json\n```\n\n### Rules\n- [ ] 检查 `status` / `generated_at` / `last_success_at` / `last_failure_at`\n- [ ] 若交易日 08:50 之后仍无当日成功记录，主动汇报阻断原因\n- [ ] 若 `status` 为 `GENERATION_FAILED` 或 `PUSH_FAILED`，主动汇报错误摘要与日志路径\n- [ ] 若已成功且无新增变化，保持安静\n\n## Quant Research Mainline Health\n\n### Command\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\npython3 scripts/run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py\n```\n\n### Output\n- `research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_YYYYMMDD.json`\n- 终端摘要：`🩺 量化投研主链巡检：OK/WARN/ALERT`\n\n### Rules\n- [ ] 检查退出码与 `overall_status`"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":7,"aggregated":"# Checklist: Heartbeat Quant Ops\n\n## 08:50 Morning News Push Check\n\n### State File\n```bash\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/global_market_morning_0850_state.json\n```\n\n### Rules\n- [ ] 检查 `status` / `generated_at` / `last_success_at` / `last_failure_at`\n- [ ] 若交易日 08:50 之后仍无当日成功记录，主动汇报阻断原因\n- [ ] 若 `status` 为 `GENERATION_FAILED` 或 `PUSH_FAILED`，主动汇报错误摘要与日志路径\n- [ ] 若已成功且无新增变化，保持安静\n\n## Quant Research Mainline Health\n\n### Command\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\npython3 scripts/run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py\n```\n\n### Output\n- `research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_YYYYMMDD.md`\n- `research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_YYYYMMDD.json`\n- 终端摘要：`🩺 量化投研主链巡检：OK/WARN/ALERT`\n\n### Rules\n- [ ] 检查退出码与 `overall_status`","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773933073480}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb98a114","parentId":"666dd95d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:11:59.650Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the heartbeat for quant ops. Let me now create a more robust continuous task runner mechanism. The key issue is that heartbeats run in isolated sessions and can't automatically advance a multi-step task in the main session.However, I can do something more practical: create a cron-triggered \"active task runner\" that checks if there's an ACTIVE_TASK.md with items to process, and if so, spawns a sub-agent to continue the task. This way, after completing a step and updating ACTIVE_TASK.md, the cron job would trigger the next step.\n\nBut actually, the user said they already have the ACTIVE_TASK.md mechanism and it still doesn't work. \n\nThe real issue is that the ACTIVE_TASK.md is only read when the user sends a new message, so there's no automatic trigger to continue from where we left off. I should either add a heartbeat that monitors for new items in the ACTIVE_TASK.md and resumes the task, or configure a cron job to periodically check and continue the work automatically.\n\nThe heartbeat approach seems more aligned with the existing setup, but the challenge is that the heartbeat runs in a separate session while the main task is in the active session. A dedicated cron job that specifically checks the ACTIVE_TASK.md and continues execution would be more reliable.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the core issue might be simpler: after completing a step and updating the ACTIVE_TASK.md, the agent is sending a message back to the user which ends the turn, so even if a new session starts from a heartbeat or message, it wouldn't automatically know to continue from the next step. I need to ensure the system recognizes the next action without relying on user input to trigger the continuation.","thinkingSignature":"437f0deabd927eee1d123888ccbca88f252ed81ab7beff379e135e9c0c575bbf"},{"type":"text","text":"我来设计一个真正能在步骤之间自动推进的机制：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4q05p5l894ne_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_active_task_continuer.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\n主动任务续跑器 - 用于在多步骤任务完成后自动推进下一项\n\n当 ACTIVE_TASK.md 中有：\n- Status: active\n- Next: 有待执行项\n则自动推进到下一项\n\n机制：\n- 此脚本由 heartbeat 或 cron 触发\n- 读取 ACTIVE_TASK.md，如 Next 有内容 → 发送消息到 main session 触发继续执行\n- main session 收到消息后，从 ACTIVE_TASK.md 读取 Current，开始下一项\n\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport sys\nimport time\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nTASK_FILE = ROOT / 'checklists' / 'ACTIVE_TASK.md'\nSTATE_FILE = ROOT / 'memory' / 'active_task_continuer_state.json'\n\n\ndef read_state() -> dict:\n    if STATE_FILE.exists():\n        return json.loads(STATE_FILE.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))\n    return {}\n\n\ndef write_state(state: dict) -> None:\n    STATE_FILE.write_text(json.dumps(state, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2), encoding='utf-8')\n\n\ndef read_task_file() -> dict:\n    \"\"\"解析 ACTIVE_TASK.md，返回关键字段。\"\"\"\n    if not TASK_FILE.exists():\n        return {'status': 'none', 'current': '', 'next': [], 'completed': []}\n\n    text = TASK_FILE.read_text(encoding='utf-8')\n    result = {'status': '', 'current': '', 'next': [], 'completed': [], 'goal': ''}\n\n    for line in text.splitlines():\n        line = line.strip()\n        if line.startswith('Status:'):\n            result['status'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n        elif line.startswith('Current:'):\n            result['current'] = line.split(':', 1)[1].strip()\n        elif line.startswith('- [') and 'Current' not in result:\n            # Completed item like \"- [2026-03-19] ...\"\n            pass\n        elif line.startswith('- [') and result['current']:\n            result['next'].append(line.lstrip('- '))\n        elif line.startswith('## Completed'):\n            # Stop parsing next items\n            break\n\n    return result\n\n\ndef send_continue_signal(task_name: str, next_item: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"发送继续信号到 main session via openclaw message.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    msg = (\n        f\"【自动续跑】任务「{task_name}」检测到待执行项：\\n\\n\"\n        f\"**下一项**：{next_item}\\n\\n\"\n        f\"请继续执行。\"\n    )\n    # Send to self via the running gateway session\n    # Using openclaw's built-in mechanism to deliver a message to the main session\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            ['openclaw', 'message', 'send', '--session', 'main', '--message', msg],\n            capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=10\n        )\n        return result.returncode == 0\n    except Exception:\n        return False\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='主动任务续跑器')\n    parser.add_argument('--dry-run', action='store_true')\n    parser.add_argument('--force', action='store_true', help='忽略 cooldowm，强制触发')\n    parser.add_argument('--cooldown-min', type=int, default=30, help='两次续跑最小间隔（分钟）')\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    task = read_task_file()\n    status = task.get('status', '')\n    current = task.get('current', '')\n    next_items = task.get('next', [])\n\n    state = read_state()\n    last_run = float(state.get('last_run', 0))\n    last_next = state.get('last_next', '')\n\n    # 检查状态\n    if status == 'done':\n        print(f\"[SKIP] Status={status}, task completed. ({TASK_FILE})\")\n        return\n    if status == 'none' or not TASK_FILE.exists():\n        print(f\"[SKIP] No active task found. ({TASK_FILE})\")\n        return\n    if status != 'active':\n        print(f\"[SKIP] Status={status}, not active. ({TASK_FILE})\")\n        return\n\n    if not next_items:\n        print(f\"[SKIP] No next items. Current='{current}'\")\n        return\n\n    # Cooldown 检查\n    if not args.force:\n        elapsed_min = (time.time() - last_run) / 60\n        if elapsed_min < args.cooldown_min:\n            print(f\"[SKIP] Cooldown: {elapsed_min:.1f}min < {args.cooldown_min}min since last run\")\n            return\n        # 如果 next item 和上次相同，还在处理中，跳过\n        if next_items[0] == last_next and elapsed_min < 5:\n            print(f\"[SKIP] Same next item '{next_items[0]}' still processing (last_run={elapsed_min:.1f}min ago)\")\n            return\n\n    next_item = next_items[0]\n\n    if args.dry_run:\n        print(f\"[DRY-RUN] Would send continue signal for: {next_item}\")\n        return\n\n    # 发送继续信号\n    goal = task.get('goal', '当前任务')\n    ok = send_continue_signal(goal, next_item)\n\n    if ok:\n        state['last_run'] = time.time()\n        state['last_next'] = next_item\n        write_state(state)\n        print(f\"[OK] Sent continue signal for: {next_item}\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"[FAIL] Could not send continue signal. Check openclaw gateway is running.\")\n        print(f\"[INFO] Task: {goal}\")\n        print(f\"[INFO] Next: {next_item}\")\n        print(f\"[INFO] To continue manually, send me a message with: 继续执行\")\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":118901,"output":1675,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":144869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933073493}}
