{"type":"message","id":"a0cc5837","parentId":"5fd9d3f4","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:12:16.906Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, using `openclaw message send --session main` won't work easily. The tool I have is the `sessions_send` tool, not a CLI command. And the message would just deliver text to the main session, but wouldn't actually trigger the session to pick up the next item from ACTIVE_TASK.md.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - the most reliable approach is:1. When the main session finishes one step, it sends a message to itself (or uses a tool that triggers the next step)\n2. OR the main session uses `sessions_spawn` with mode=\"session\" to continue\n3. OR the heartbeat is configured to check ACTIVE_TASK.md and send the right instructions to the main session\n\n\n4. \nThe cleanest solution is to have the main session check ACTIVE_TASK.md at the end of each response and spawn a sub-agent if there are more steps to execute. But the real constraint here is that OpenClaw sessions don't automatically continue on their own - they need an explicit trigger. The session is only active while a user is actively communicating with it, so once a task finishes and the response is sent, there's no mechanism to automatically kick off the next step unless I configure a heartbeat to do that.\n\nLooking at the heartbeat rules, they only handle periodic maintenance tasks, not multi-step task chains. The user's actual problem is different though - when they say the system stops after completing one step, I think they're saying the session just ends after my final reply in a turn. The real issue is probably that I need to use `sessions_yield` to explicitly hand control back to the orchestrator rather than ending the turn with a message. Or more likely, I should be structuring this so that after completing step N, I spawn a sub-agent to handle step N+1 instead of trying to do everything in the main session.","thinkingSignature":"bf796aedf4733b0f4faf11bf821f9fee30e342fb043f13940743c204af83cd5f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zjgq8tnkt7hl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_active_task_continuer.py --dry-run 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120567,"output":423,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145283,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933119718}}
{"type":"message","id":"6da07739","parentId":"a0cc5837","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:12:17.032Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zjgq8tnkt7hl_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[SKIP] Status=done, task completed. (/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":83,"aggregated":"[SKIP] Status=done, task completed. (/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md)","cwd":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773933137022}}
{"type":"message","id":"b80366e3","parentId":"6da07739","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:12:46.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the ACTIVE_TASK.md is done. Let me now think about what the user really needs. They want a mechanism that when a multi-step task is active, after completing one step, the system automatically continues to the next without waiting for a new user message.\n\nThe problem is architectural: the session-based architecture doesn't have an automatic continuation mechanism. Each message is a turn, and turns don't automatically chain.\n\nBut the heartbeat CAN trigger new actions. So I can create a heartbeat that checks if there's an active task and if so, spawns a sub-agent to continue.\n\nHowever, looking at the existing heartbeat, it's a `main-session` poll that just reads files and reacts. It doesn't spawn sub-agents.\n\n\nI'm weighing three approaches: creating a dedicated cron job that periodically checks and spawns sub-agents to continue active tasks, integrating this check into the existing heartbeat, or just accepting that multi-step tasks need explicit continuation triggers between turns. The cron approach feels like the cleanest way to handle automatic progression without modifying the core session architecture.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the simplest path forward is to just be more intentional about continuation within the same session—if I'm actively working on a multi-step task, I should call `sessions_spawn` to hand off the next step rather than ending my turn and waiting for the user to prompt me again.\n\nBut thinking about it more, the real issue is that I should use the `active_task_cli.py` to atomically advance the task state to the next item, and then in my response, I should explicitly spawn a sub-agent or send a message to myself to continue execution. That's more reliable than hoping the user will prompt me to keep going.\n\nActually, wait—let me reconsider. If I use `sessions_yield`, that hands control back to the orchestrator and lets the next message continue the task, but the session would still end unless there's a heartbeat polling to keep it alive. The heartbeat already has periodic maintenance checks configured, so I could leverage that existing mechanism instead of building something new.\n\nThe heartbeat runs every few minutes and reads the HEARTBEAT.md file, but it's not checking for active tasks. The real problem is that when a task is actively running in the main session, the heartbeat doesn't know about it—it just sees the status as done or unknown. So I need to design a solution where the heartbeat can detect an active task and continue it without waiting for the user to send another message.\n\nMy approach: create a cron job that runs every 30 minutes and checks if ACTIVE_TASK.md has an active status with pending items, then automatically spawns a sub-agent to continue where it left off. The main session would just need to keep the task active in that file. This way, there's no need to modify how the heartbeat works or add complex inter-session communication.","thinkingSignature":"24f79f29210d7b7d213dac60f9c6768334043d6742f257fcd6ecc6ee4177a242"},{"type":"text","text":"现在配置一个定时任务，每 30 分钟检查一次 ACTIVE_TASK.md，有 pending 项就自动续跑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l8akpk65g4bi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"主动任务续跑检查\" \\\n  --session isolated \\\n  --cron \"*/30 * * * *\" \\\n  --tz \"Asia/Shanghai\" \\\n  --message \"执行以下检查并续跑：\n1. python3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_active_task_continuer.py --cooldown-min 25\n2. 如果有 active task 且 Next 有内容：发送摘要报告到飞书 DM，说明已触发续跑\n\n报告格式：\n- 当前任务：{goal}\n- 状态：{status}\n- 下一项：{next_item}\n- 如无需续跑，保持安静。\" \\\n  --announce \\\n  --to \"user:ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\" \\\n  --timeout-seconds 60 \\\n  2>&1 | grep -v \"^\\[plugins\\]\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120311,"output":816,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":145420,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933137036}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0d7df21","parentId":"b80366e3","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:12:49.762Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l8akpk65g4bi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"│\n◇  Doctor warnings ──────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                        │\n│  - State dir migration skipped: target already exists  │\n│    (/Users/ling/.openclaw). Remove or merge manually.  │\n│                                                        │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\n{\n  \"id\": \"b2818217-e801-46b9-86e2-ee9420085900\",\n  \"name\": \"主动任务续跑检查\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1773933169701,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1773933169701,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"*/30 * * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"执行以下检查并续跑：\\n1. python3 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_active_task_continuer.py --cooldown-min 25\\n2. 如果有 active task 且 Next 有内容：发送摘要报告到飞书 DM，说明已触发续跑\\n\\n报告格式：\\n- 当前任务：{goal}\\n- 状态：{status}\\n- 下一项：{next_item}\\n- 如无需续跑，保持安静。\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 60\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"last\",\n    \"to\": \"user:ou_83b02a0239e70fc8a4bf0b79aa8f9db7\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773934200000\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3501,"aggregated":"│\n◇  Doctor warnings ──────────────────────────────────────╮\n│                                                        │\n│  - State dir migration skipped: target already exists  │\n│    (/Users/ling/.openclaw). Remove or merge manually.  │\n│                                                        │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\n{\n  \"id\": \"b2818217-e801-46b9-86e2-ee9420085900\",\n  \"name\": \"主动任务