{"type":"message","id":"1d5efb84","parentId":"3a4a0c3d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:16:14.185Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether the 30-minute cron task will consume a lot of tokens. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The cron task runs every 30 minutes, which is 48 times per day\n2. Each run executes a Python script (`run_active_task_continuer.py`) and if it finds active tasks, it spawns a new isolated session\n3. If ACTIVE_TASK is \"done\", the script just exits quickly with \"[SKIP]\", consuming minimal tokens\n4. Only when there's actual work to do would it spawn an isolated session\n\nThe token cost breakdown:\n- Most runs: script does a quick file read + exit → very minimal tokens (just the Python process startup + file read)\n\n\n- When triggering: isolated session spawn + report delivery to Feishu\n\nFor 48 runs/day of a simple Python script that just reads a file and exits, the token cost is negligible. The real concern would be if I'm spawning heavy isolated sessions each time, but most of those runs would just be quick exits when there's nothing to do.\n\nThe bigger question is whether the Feishu announcement for each heartbeat would create excessive noise. But if the task is already done, the script skips entirely without messaging, so that shouldn't be an issue. I'm thinking through the most efficient setup—maybe running the check every 30 minutes is already reasonable, though I could also go with 15 minutes or a simpler approach. The openclaw cron sessions themselves don't consume tokens unless the gateway processes them, and if the script exits immediately with \"[SKIP]\", it shouldn't trigger a full agent turn. The real issue is that the Feishu announcement would fire even when there's nothing to do, so I should probably disable that default behavior and only announce when there's actual work to report.\n\nLooking at the cron configuration more closely, I see the message text still has literal `\\n` characters instead of actual newlines, which is a formatting bug that won't break anything but means the announcement message won't look right. Still, the most practical solution is to keep the 30-minute frequency and silence announcements when there's nothing to announce.","thinkingSignature":"f9f45b89398f8016b9c10e18f1c3fb7e7dc67dee480da55d7f17ac82624cf1cd"},{"type":"text","text":"不会。分析一下：\n\n**48次/天的消耗分布：**\n- 47次：ACTIVE_TASK 是 done → 脚本读一个文件、发现 done、立刻退出 `[SKIP]`\n  - 消耗：≈ 几百个 token（Python 进程启动 + 一次文件读）\n- 1次（假设有 active 任务）：需要发信号触发继续\n  - 消耗：一个轻量 isolated session turn\n\n**真正影响 token 的只有活跃任务在跑的时候**。没有活跃任务时就是空转。\n\n不过我可以优化一下——**把 Feishu 通知去掉**，只在有东西要续跑时才出声：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i1kaqidie0op_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron list 2>&1 | grep -v \"^\\[plugins\\]\" | grep \"主动任务续跑\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80,"output":610,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":120663,"totalTokens":145646,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933349371}}
