{"type":"message","id":"d9774d74","parentId":"2aabaacd","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:25:46.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! There's a `memory-core` plugin (stock:memory-core) that's loaded, and several other memory plugins available. The `memory-pro` the script is looking for doesn't exist as a separate command - it's likely from one of the memory plugins.\n\nBut the key thing is that `openclaw memory list --json` doesn't work - `openclaw memory` has `status`, `index`, and `search` commands, not `list` or `import`.\n\nThe `memory-pro` plugin/script the script uses is likely from a specific third-party source that isn't installed. \n\nLet me check if there's a `memory-pro` npm package or CLI tool available.","thinkingSignature":"48a841801705c4e448e4eb2aa3d5254e2f445606067fb34953b86f1dd610b36f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_py6hbehtyxqu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"npm list -g 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"memory\\|mcp\" | head -10; ls ~/.openclaw/plugins/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":117889,"output":199,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":142381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933932217}}
