{"type":"message","id":"a9eb7623","parentId":"28dc8c5e","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:26:02.364Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `memory-pro` npm package installed. The `memory-pro` command doesn't exist anywhere. The script `bridge_codex_chat_to_openclaw.py` is fundamentally broken because it depends on `memory-pro` which was never installed or has been removed.\n\nThe fix options:\n1. Install `memory-pro` (but there's no package/skill for it)\n2. Rewrite the script to not use `memory-pro`\n\nSince `memory-pro` is not available, I should make the script gracefully handle its absence. The simplest fix is to make `existing_memory_ids` return an empty set when `memory-pro` is not available, and make the import skip gracefully.\n\n\nNow I'm looking at how to patch the script itself. The core issue is that when `memory-pro list` fails, the whole operation should continue without crashing. I need to add error handling around those `memory-pro` calls so they fail gracefully instead of propagating exceptions.","thinkingSignature":"5c7e46dfbac99eafdc72ea49f2bdd15955a7e9df85b4e445d336fa916617c802"},{"type":"text","text":"`memory-pro` 根本不存在——这个插件/命令从未安装过。脚本依赖它，所以每次都崩。修复方案：让脚本在 `memory-pro` 不可用时 graceful fallback，不崩溃：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c22x1dyy1w6l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts && python3 << 'PATCH'\nimport re\n\nwith open('bridge_codex_chat_to_openclaw.py', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Replace existing_memory_ids with a graceful version\nold_func = '''def existing_memory_ids(scope: str) -> set[str]:\n    items = mpp.run_openclaw(\"memory-pro\", \"list\", \"--scope\", scope, \"--json\", capture_json=True)\n    return {str(item.get(\"id\", \"\")).strip() for item in items if item.get(\"id\")}'''\n\nnew_func = '''def existing_memory_ids(scope: str) -> set[str]:\n    \"\"\"List existing memory IDs. Falls back to empty set if memory-pro unavailable.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        items = mpp.run_openclaw(\"memory-pro\", \"list\", \"--scope\", scope, \"--json\", capture_json=True)\n        return {str(item.get(\"id\", \"\")).strip() for item in items if item.get(\"id\")}\n    except Exception as e:\n        import sys\n        print(f\"[WARN] memory-pro unavailable ({e}), skipping dedup check\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return set()  # Skip dedup - will import all; harmless duplicate on next run'''\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_func, new_func)\n\n# Also wrap the import call\nold_import = '''        mpp.run_openclaw(\"memory-pro\", \"import\", str(import_path), \"--scope\", scope)'''\nnew_import = '''        try:\n            mpp.run_openclaw(\"memory-pro\", \"import\", str(import_path), \"--scope\", scope)\n        except Exception as e:\n            import sys\n            print(f\"[WARN] memory-pro import unavailable ({e}), memories saved to {import_path} for manual import\", file=sys.stderr)'''\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_import, new_import)\n\nwith open('bridge_codex_chat_to_openclaw.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint('patched ok')\nPATCH"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":118113,"output":673,"cacheRead":24293,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":143079,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773933947429}}
